Description: Five joining fragments of rim and body of pottery eye cup; glaze fired red-brown; interior glazed with two added red bands lined in white; exterior: top of lip glazed; below, a pair of painted eyes with arching eyebrows and spiral forms to denote the nose; two verticals preserved to left and two bands below the handle zone.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 256, no. 3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.467)
